bb0793f8-45a6-406d-8b2a-90fd500c7fad.title: Sloane
bb0793f8-45a6-406d-8b2a-90fd500c7fad.text:
Ah, but I can see you are already as strong as is
possible! Perhaps you have come to me to purchase a
Cape of Strength, and thus join the elite few who have
mastered this exacting skill?

9dec1bfe-d150-4d37-ae9a-bd8fd2076be3.title: Sloane
9dec1bfe-d150-4d37-ae9a-bd8fd2076be3.text:
As an additional recognition of your achievement, the
Cape of Strength can teleport you to our guild.

options.text: May I claim my tokens please?

3ea7ae9a-d5ff-42eb-9334-c855b6389250.title: Sloane
3ea7ae9a-d5ff-42eb-9334-c855b6389250.text:
Ahh, the shot put is a great test of strength and can be
quite rewarding. Mind you do it properly though, you
might want to dust your hands with some powdery
substance first. It'll give better grip.

156c8626-ea59-4cdf-8703-5b55c02ffd1c.title: <player>
156c8626-ea59-4cdf-8703-5b55c02ffd1c.text: I'll remember that. What should I use?

1b781b80-cf78-4d7d-b01c-f5a5a2a01f1d.title: Sloane
1b781b80-cf78-4d7d-b01c-f5a5a2a01f1d.text:
I personally prefer ground ashes, it makes a nice fine
powder and gives some really good grip.

21834ab5-bd45-491c-8aee-acfe87639f5b.title: Sloane
21834ab5-bd45-491c-8aee-acfe87639f5b.text:
Basically you'll need to go in there, make sure you've
got nothing cluttering up your hands, pick up a shot
and throw it.... depending upon your technique, you
can get quite long throws.

ffc0995d-d51b-476c-aa18-2f0c7350f473.title: Sloane
ffc0995d-d51b-476c-aa18-2f0c7350f473.text:
Yes indeed it is. Have to be mighty strong to wield it
too.

5e45f4dd-d4e9-4214-a908-6104c9e8b1a3.title: <player>
5e45f4dd-d4e9-4214-a908-6104c9e8b1a3.text: But you don't look that strong!

e4268372-6459-4cc1-a169-5d44e94927e8.title: Sloane
e4268372-6459-4cc1-a169-5d44e94927e8.text:
Maybe, maybe not, but I still had to beat a Barbarian
to get it. Mind you, usually they don't part with them.
This was an unusual circumstance.

a6107580-877c-47dd-a17e-64a61a831080.title: Sloane
a6107580-877c-47dd-a17e-64a61a831080.text:
I bet him he couldn't catch a squirrel whilst still holding
his axe but that I could... and that if I won I'd get his
axe.

ade50914-867c-40ae-9798-071cf0553c1f.title: Sloane
ade50914-867c-40ae-9798-071cf0553c1f.text:
He went running after the squirrel... nearly caught it
too... it shot up a tree and he tried to climb up it, only
got a bit tangled up with his axe cause he couldn't hang
on to it at the same time... he fell out of the tree and it

d4394628-ec56-4ce0-9a33-31aca9918b9d.title: Sloane
d4394628-ec56-4ce0-9a33-31aca9918b9d.text:
I simply went and chopped the tree down with this big
old axe, still holding it. The squirrel was so petrified it
simply jumped straight out of the tree onto me, I won
the axe and let the poor creature go!

9c2738c0-2703-48f7-88dc-57fa05b9e775.title: <player>
9c2738c0-2703-48f7-88dc-57fa05b9e775.text: I sense a moral in there somewhere.

07ecb4d9-a080-4760-9408-f2a605ba129a.title: Sloane
07ecb4d9-a080-4760-9408-f2a605ba129a.text:
Aye indeed. Brawn isn't all you need to wield a big axe,
brains are required too!

acb1ec4e-d31e-400d-b8c3-2fd86538b3e4.title: <player>
acb1ec4e-d31e-400d-b8c3-2fd86538b3e4.text: May I claim my tokens please?
